1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 24-05-17 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to the county road system.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 24-05-17 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 24-05-17. Responsibility for county road system.
7 The boards of county commissioners in their respective counties have the sole authority
8 and responsibility to acquire land for, construct, maintain, and operate the county road system
9 as designated and selected by them. If a board of county commissioners determines a local
10 road meets the criteria in section 24 - 05 - 16 and is under the jurisdiction of the township, the
11 board of county commissioners shall notify the township of its intention to add the road to the
12 county system. The board of county commissions shall hold a public meeting to receive input on
13 the county's intention to add the road to the county system. Following the public meeting, the
14 board of county commissioners shall make a decision at its next scheduled meeting regarding
15 adding the road to the county system.
